CL:0000066.name: epithelial cell
CL:0000066.clDescription: A cell that is usually found in a two-dimensional sheet with a free surface. The cell has a cytoskeleton that allows for tight cell to cell contact and for cell polarity where apical part is directed towards the lumen and the basal part to the basal lamina.

CL:0000084.name: T cell
CL:0000084.clDescription: A type of lymphocyte whose defining characteristic is the expression of a T cell receptor complex.

CL:0000097.name: mast cell
CL:0000097.clDescription: A cell that is found in almost all tissues containing numerous basophilic granules and capable of releasing large amounts of histamine and heparin upon activation. Progenitors leave bone marrow and mature in connective and mucosal tissue. Mature mast cells are found in all tissues, except the bloodstream. Their phenotype is CD117-high, CD123-negative, CD193-positive, CD200R3-positive, and FceRI-high. Stem-cell factor (KIT-ligand; SCF) is the main controlling signal of their survival and development.

CL:0000115.name: endothelial cell
CL:0000115.clDescription: An endothelial cell comprises the outermost layer or lining of anatomical structures and can be squamous or cuboidal. In mammals, endothelial cell has vimentin filaments and is derived from the mesoderm.

CL:0000148.name: melanocyte
CL:0000148.clDescription: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. Contains melanin-filled pigment granules, which gives a brown to black appearance.

CL:0000169.name: type B pancreatic cell
CL:0000169.clDescription: A cell that secretes insulin and is located towards the center of the islets of Langerhans.

CL:0000171.name: pancreatic A cell
CL:0000171.clDescription: A type of enteocrine cell found in the periphery of the islets of Langerhans that secretes glucagon.
synonyms: alpha cell of islet of Langerhans

CL:0000173.name: pancreatic D cell
CL:0000173.clDescription: A D cell located in the pancreas. Peripherally placed within the islets like type A cells; contains somatostatin.

CL:0000187.name: muscle cell
CL:0000187.clDescription: A mature contractile cell, commonly known as a myocyte. This cell has as part of its cytoplasm myofibrils organized in various patterns.

CL:0000188.name: cell of skeletal muscle
CL:0000188.clDescription: A somatic cell located in skeletal muscle.

CL:0000192.name: smooth muscle cell
CL:0000192.clDescription: A non-striated, elongated, spindle-shaped cell found lining the digestive tract, uterus, and blood vessels. They develop from specialized myoblasts (smooth muscle myoblast).

CL:0000235.name: macrophage
CL:0000235.clDescription: A mononuclear phagocyte present in variety of tissues, typically differentiated from monocytes, capable of phagocytosing a variety of extracellular particulate material, including immune complexes, microorganisms, and dead cells.

CL:0000453.name: Langerhans cell
CL:0000453.clDescription: Langerhans cell is a conventional dendritic cell that has plasma membrane part CD207. A Langerhans cell is a stellate dendritic cell of myeloid origin, that appears clear on light microscopy and has a dark-staining, indented nucleus and characteristic inclusions (Birbeck granules) in the cytoplasm; Langerhans cells are found principally in the stratum spinosum of the epidermis, but they also occur in other stratified epithelia and have been identified in the lung, lymph nodes, spleen, and thymus.

CL:0000492.name: CD4-positive helper T cell
CL:0000492.clDescription: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that cooperates with other lymphocytes via direct contact or cytokine release to initiate a variety of immune functions.

CL:0000499.name: stromal cell
CL:0000499.clDescription: A connective tissue cell of an organ found in the loose connective tissue. These are most often associated with the uterine mucosa and the ovary as well as the hematopoietic system and elsewhere.

CL:0000738.name: leukocyte
CL:0000738.clDescription: An achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages capable of ameboid movement, found in blood or other tissue.

CL:0000786.name: plasma cell
CL:0000786.clDescription: A terminally differentiated, post-mitotic, antibody secreting cell of the B cell lineage with the phenotype CD138-positive, surface immunonoglobulin-negative, and MHC Class II-negative. Plasma cells are oval or round with extensive rough endoplasmic reticulum, a well-developed Golgi apparatus, and a round nucleus having a characteristic cartwheel heterochromatin pattern and are devoted to producing large amounts of immunoglobulin.

CL:0000787.name: memory B cell
CL:0000787.clDescription: A memory B cell is a mature B cell that is long-lived, readily activated upon re-encounter of its antigenic determinant, and has been selected for expression of higher affinity immunoglobulin. This cell type has the phenotype CD19-positive, CD20-positive, MHC Class II-positive, and CD138-negative.

CL:0000788.name: naive B cell
CL:0000788.clDescription: A naive B cell is a mature B cell that has the phenotype surface IgD-positive, surface IgM-positive, CD20-positive, CD27-negative and that has not yet been activated by antigen in the periphery.

CL:0000794.name: CD8-positive, alpha-beta cytotoxic T cell
CL:0000794.clDescription: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that is capable of killing target cells in an antigen specific manner with the phenotype perforin-positive and granzyme B-positive.

CL:0000814.name: mature NK T cell
CL:0000814.clDescription: A mature alpha-beta T cell of a distinct lineage that bears natural killer markers and a T cell receptor specific for a limited set of ligands. NK T cells have activation and regulatory roles particularly early in an immune response.

CL:0000815.name: regulatory T cell
CL:0000815.clDescription: A T cell which regulates overall immune responses as well as the responses of other T cell subsets through direct cell-cell contact and cytokine release.

CL:0000895.name: naive thymus-derived CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000895.clDescription: An antigen inexperienced CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive and CD62L-positive. This cell type develops in the thymus. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high, and CD44-low.
synonyms: naive thymus-derived CD4-positive, alpha-beta T lymphocyte

CL:0000897.name: CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell
CL:0000897.clDescription: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has differentiated into a memory T cell.

CL:0000900.name: naive thymus-derived CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000900.clDescription: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has not experienced activation via antigen contact and has the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CCR7-positive and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high and CD44-low.
synonyms: naive thymus-dervied CD8-positive, alpha-beta T lymphocyte

CL:0000909.name: CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell
CL:0000909.clDescription: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has differentiated into a memory T cell.

CL:0002064.name: pancreatic acinar cell
CL:0002064.clDescription: A secretory cell found in pancreatic acini that secretes digestive enzymes and mucins. This cell is a typical zymogenic cell, have a basal nucleus and basophilic cytoplasm consisting of regular arrays of granular endoplasmic reticulum with mitochondria and dense secretory granules.

CL:0002079.name: pancreatic ductal cell
CL:0002079.clDescription: Epithelial cell found in the ducts of the pancreas. This cell type contributes to the high luminal pH.

CL:0002275.name: pancreatic PP cell
CL:0002275.clDescription: A PP cell located in the islets of the pancreas.

CL:0002394.name: CD141-positive myeloid dendritic cell
CL:0002394.clDescription: A myeloid dendritic cell found in the blood, lymph nodes, tonsil, bone marrow, and spleen that is CD141-positive (BDCA-3), XCR1-positive, and Clec9A-positive. This cell-type can cross-present antigen to CD8-positive T cells and can produce inteferon-beta.

CL:0002399.name: CD1c-positive myeloid dendritic cell
CL:0002399.clDescription: A myeloid dendritic cell found in the blood that is CD1c-positive.

CL:0002410.name: pancreatic stellate cell
CL:0002410.clDescription: A cell that is found in the periacinar space of the exocrine pancreas and in perivascular and periductal regions of the pancreas, and has long cytoplasmic processes that encircle the base of the acinus. Expresses several intermediate filament proteins including vimentin and nestin. Shares many of the characteristics of hepatatic stellate cells, but not stellate cells of the central nervous system. Upon activation, this cell type undergoes morphological and gene expression changes that make the cell suggestive of being a type of myofibroblast.

CL:0000000.name: cell
CL:0000000.clDescription: A material entity of anatomical origin (part of or deriving from an organism) that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

CL:0000003.name: native cell
CL:0000003.clDescription: A cell that is found in a natural setting, which includes multicellular organism cells 'in vivo' (i.e. part of an organism), and unicellular organisms 'in environment' (i.e. part of a natural environment).

CL:0000057.name: fibroblast
CL:0000057.clDescription: A connective tissue cell which secretes an extracellular matrix rich in collagen and other macromolecules. Flattened and irregular in outline with branching processes; appear fusiform or spindle-shaped.

CL:0000068.name: duct epithelial cell
CL:0000068.clDescription: An epithelial cell that is part of a duct.

CL:0000083.name: epithelial cell of pancreas
CL:0000083.clDescription: An epithelial cell of the pancreas.

CL:0000145.name: professional antigen presenting cell
CL:0000145.clDescription: A cell capable of processing and presenting lipid and protein antigens to T cells in order to initiate an immune response.

CL:0000147.name: pigment cell
CL:0000147.clDescription: A pigment cell is a cell that contains pigment granules.

CL:0000150.name: glandular epithelial cell
CL:0000150.clDescription: A specialized epithelial cell that is capable of synthesizing and secreting certain biomolecules.

CL:0000151.name: secretory cell
CL:0000151.clDescription: A cell that specializes in controlled release of one or more substances.

CL:0000152.name: exocrine cell
CL:0000152.clDescription: A cell of an exocrine gland; i.e. a gland that discharges its secretion via a duct.

CL:0000163.name: endocrine cell
CL:0000163.clDescription: A cell of an endocrine gland, ductless glands that secrete substances which are released directly into the circulation and which influence metabolism and other body functions.

CL:0000164.name: enteroendocrine cell
CL:0000164.clDescription: An endocrine cell that is located in the epithelium of the gastrointestinal tract or in the pancreas.

CL:0000183.name: contractile cell
CL:0000183.clDescription: A cell whose primary function is to shorten.

CL:0000211.name: electrically active cell
CL:0000211.clDescription: A cell whose function is determined by the generation or the reception of an electric signal.

CL:0000213.name: lining cell
CL:0000213.clDescription: A cell within an epithelial cell sheet whose main function is to act as an internal or external covering for a tissue or an organism.

CL:0000215.name: barrier cell
CL:0000215.clDescription: A cell whose primary function is to prevent the transport of stuff across compartments.

CL:0000219.name: motile cell
CL:0000219.clDescription: A cell that moves by its own activities.

CL:0000226.name: single nucleate cell
CL:0000226.clDescription: A cell with a single nucleus.

CL:0000234.name: phagocyte
CL:0000234.clDescription: Any cell capable of ingesting particulate matter via phagocytosis.

CL:0000236.name: B cell
CL:0000236.clDescription: A lymphocyte of B lineage that is capable of B cell mediated immunity.

CL:0000325.name: stuff accumulating cell
CL:0000325.clDescription: A cell that is specialised to accumulate a particular substance(s).

CL:0000393.name: electrically responsive cell
CL:0000393.clDescription: A cell whose function is determined by its response to an electric signal.

CL:0000451.name: dendritic cell
CL:0000451.clDescription: A cell of hematopoietic origin, typically resident in particular tissues, specialized in the uptake, processing, and transport of antigens to lymph nodes for the purpose of stimulating an immune response via T cell activation. These cells are lineage negative (CD3-negative, CD19-negative, CD34-negative, and CD56-negative).

CL:0000473.name: defensive cell
CL:0000473.clDescription: A cell whose primary function is to protect the organism.

CL:0000502.name: type D enteroendocrine cell
CL:0000502.clDescription: A cell found throughout the gastrointestinal tract and in the pancreas. They secrete somatostatin in both an endocrine and paracrine manner. Somatostatin inhibits gastrin, cholecystokinin, insulin, glucagon, pancreatic enzymes, and gastric hydrochloric acid. A variety of substances which inhibit gastric acid secretion (vasoactive intestinal peptide, calcitonin gene-related peptide, cholecystokinin, beta-adrenergic agonists, and gastric inhibitory peptide) are thought to act by releasing somatostatin.

CL:0000542.name: lymphocyte
CL:0000542.clDescription: A lymphocyte is a leukocyte commonly found in the blood and lymph that has the characteristics of a large nucleus, a neutral staining cytoplasm, and prominent heterochromatin.

CL:0000548.name: animal cell
CL:0000548.clDescription: A native cell that is part of some Metazoa.

CL:0000622.name: acinar cell
CL:0000622.clDescription: A secretory cell that is grouped together with other cells of the same type to form grape shaped clusters known as acini (singular acinus).

CL:0000624.name: CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000624.clDescription: A mature alpha-beta T cell that expresses an alpha-beta T cell receptor and the CD4 coreceptor.

CL:0000625.name: CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000625.clDescription: A T cell expressing an alpha-beta T cell receptor and the CD8 coreceptor.

CL:0000696.name: PP cell
CL:0000696.clDescription: A cell that stores and secretes pancreatic polypeptide hormone.

CL:0000763.name: myeloid cell
CL:0000763.clDescription: A cell of the monocyte, granulocyte, mast cell, megakaryocyte, or erythroid lineage.

CL:0000766.name: myeloid leukocyte
CL:0000766.clDescription: A cell of the monocyte, granulocyte, or mast cell lineage.

CL:0000782.name: myeloid dendritic cell
CL:0000782.clDescription: A dendritic cell of the myeloid lineage.

CL:0000784.name: plasmacytoid dendritic cell
CL:0000784.clDescription: A dendritic cell type of distinct morphology, localization, and surface marker expression (CD123-positive) from other dendritic cell types and associated with early stage immune responses, particularly the release of physiologically abundant amounts of type I interferons in response to infection.

CL:0000842.name: mononuclear cell
CL:0000842.clDescription: A leukocyte with a single non-segmented nucleus in the mature form.

CL:0000898.name: naive T cell
CL:0000898.clDescription: Mature T cell not yet exposed to antigen with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD45RA-positive, and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high and CD44-low.

CL:0000945.name: lymphocyte of B lineage
CL:0000945.clDescription: A lymphocyte of B lineage with the commitment to express an immunoglobulin complex.

CL:0000946.name: antibody secreting cell
CL:0000946.clDescription: A lymphocyte of B lineage that is devoted to secreting large amounts of immunoglobulin.

CL:0000988.name: hematopoietic cell
CL:0000988.clDescription: A cell of a hematopoietic lineage.

CL:0000990.name: conventional dendritic cell
CL:0000990.clDescription: Conventional dendritic cell is a dendritic cell that is CD11c-high.

CL:0001200.name: lymphocyte of B lineage, CD19-positive
CL:0001200.clDescription: A lymphocyte of B lineage that is CD19-positive.

CL:0001201.name: B cell, CD19-positive
CL:0001201.clDescription: A B cell that is CD19-positive.

CL:0002067.name: type A enteroendocrine cell
CL:0002067.clDescription: An enteroendocrine cell that produces glucagon.

CL:0002078.name: meso-epithelial cell
CL:0002078.clDescription: Epithelial cell derived from mesoderm or mesenchyme.

CL:0002242.name: nucleate cell
CL:0002242.clDescription: A cell containing at least one nucleus.

CL:0002274.name: histamine secreting cell
CL:0002274.clDescription: A cell type that secretes histamine.

CL:0002320.name: connective tissue cell
CL:0002320.clDescription: A cell of the supporting or framework tissue of the body, arising chiefly from the embryonic mesoderm and including adipose tissue, cartilage, and bone.

CL:0002419.name: mature T cell
CL:0002419.clDescription: A T cell that expresses a T cell receptor complex and has completed T cell selection.

CL:0002371.name: somatic cell
CL:0002371.clDescription: A cell of an organism that does not pass on its genetic material to the organism's offspring (i.e. a non-germ line cell).

CL:0008000.name: non-striated muscle cell
CL:0008000.clDescription: Any muscle cell in which the fibers are not organised into sarcomeres.

CL:0008007.name: visceral muscle cell
CL:0008007.clDescription: A muscle cell that is part of some visceral muscle.

CL:0008024.name: pancreatic endocrine cell
CL:0008024.clDescription: An endocrine cell that is part of the pancreas.

CL:0000785.name: mature B cell
CL:0000785.clDescription: A B cell that is mature, having left the bone marrow. Initially, these cells are IgM-positive and IgD-positive, and they can be activated by antigen.

CL:0000789.name: alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000789.clDescription: A T cell that expresses an alpha-beta T cell receptor complex.

CL:0000791.name: mature alpha-beta T cell
CL:0000791.clDescription: A alpha-beta T cell that has a mature phenotype.

CL:0000813.name: memory T cell
CL:0000813.clDescription: A long-lived, antigen-experienced T cell that has acquired a memory phenotype including distinct surface markers and the ability to differentiate into an effector T cell upon antigen reexposure.

CL:1001433.name: epithelial cell of exocrine pancreas
CL:1001433.clDescription: An epithelial cell of the exocrine pancreas.

CL:1001599.name: pancreas exocrine glandular cell
CL:1001599.clDescription: Glandular cell of exocrine pancreas epithelium. Example: pancreatic acinar cell, glandular cells in pancreatic canaliculi, glandular cells in pancreatic ducts.
